In case someone needs it, here is my workaround at the moment, this is a personalized handler after removing unicode from primitives definition :

    import jsonpickle
    import jsonpickle.handlers
    import jsonpickle.util

    # warning : monkeypatching
    jsonpickle.util.PRIMITIVES = str, int, float, bool, long

    class UnicodeHandler(jsonpickle.handlers.BaseHandler):

        def flatten(self, obj, data):
            data['value'] = obj.encode('utf-8')
            return data

        def restore(self, data):
            return unicode(data['value'])


    jsonpickle.handlers.registry.register(unicode, UnicodeHandler)


it will encode unicode as

    {
        "py/object": "__builtin__.unicode", 
        "value": "test\u00e9"
    }

